Description: University of Miami Miller School of Medicine Brain Endowment Bank
Laboratory of Translational Neurobiology led by Principal Investigator Dr. Hongxin Dong MD PhD at Northwestern University.

Located at UCSF, The Human Brain and Spinal Fluid Resource Center (HBSFRC) is a brain bank for neuroscientists. The Center collects, stores, and distributes the highest quality of pre- and post-mortem tissues, including brain, spinal cord, cerebrospinal fluid (CSF), serum, blood cells and urine, to be use by scientific investigators of neurological and psychiatric diseases.
